 he has worked for many years on the topic of risk communication in the context of chronic diseases when time is a crucial factor he is one of the founders of odense risk group kristiansen received an md from the university of oslo in 1972 completed his internship at the university hospital of trondheim and then worked for 10 years as a combined family physician public health officer in two remote communities in norway he received an mph degree from harvard university i 1986 and a phd from university of troms norway in 1996 kristiansen is a past president of the norwegian public health association and has served on numerous public committees in norway other affiliations professor of public health at the department of health management and health economics university of oslo norway and adjunct professor of pharmacoeconomics at the university of southern denmark at odense events & presentations the concept of risk when time is a crucial factor how to understand and how to communicate theoretical considerations and empirical findings january 25 2012 research in progress seminar ivar snb kristiansen pdf+ presentation available search chp search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 736 0815 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
